      "text": "Nicotine is one of the quickest-acting addictive drugs there is. Each puff delivers a small dose to your brain within seconds, and your brain quickly adapts by expecting more. Here's the crucial part: nicotine leaves the body almost as fast as it arrives. Levels drop sharply within half an hour and keep falling. That's why most regular smokers land somewhere near twenty a day — they're not choosing twenty, they're topping up a tank that keeps draining.\n\nSo the rhythm of your smoking was never really about pleasure or willpower. It was a chemical clock. The drug goes in, the drug drains out, a small discomfort appears, you refill. Over and over, all day, for years."
